            Where most brokers compete on lowest spreads or biggest bonuses, Saxo competes on
            quality, scope, and institutional-grade service. Understanding this distinction is
            key to evaluating whether Saxo fits your needs.
          </p>

          <h5>The Infrastructure Advantage</h5>
          <p>
            {broker?.name}'s technology infrastructure handles billions in daily trading volume.
            Execution quality, platform stability, and data feeds meet institutional standards.
            During high-volatility events when retail broker platforms may struggle, Saxo's
            infrastructure remains stable. For traders who experienced platform outages or
            requotes during market moves, this reliability has real value.
          </p>

          <h5>Research That Actually Helps</h5>
          <p>
            Most broker "research" consists of recycled news and generic analysis. Saxo's
            Strategy Team produces original macro analysis, trade ideas, and market commentary
            that rivals investment bank output. The quarterly outlooks and thematic pieces
            provide genuine insight. For traders who use fundamental analysis, this research
            represents significant value often costing thousands annually elsewhere.
          </p>

          <h5>True Multi-Asset Capability</h5>
          <p>
            Consider what's actually possible with Saxo: buy US stocks, hedge with S&P options,
            hold European ETFs, trade forex, and invest in bonds - all from one account with
            unified reporting. This isn't marketing; it's genuine capability. For investors
